<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><regulation id="LMS1573990" year.imprint="2026" date.as.at="2026-03-02" date.first.valid="2026-04-01" gazette-only="no" imperial="no" date.gazetted="2026-03-05" date.signed="2026-03-02" sr.no="36" year="2026" series="secondary-legislation" date.terminated="nulldate" sr.type="order"><cover id="LMS1573991"><title>Social Security (Rates of Benefits and Allowances) Order 2026</title><gg>Cindy Kiro, Governor-General</gg><made><heading>Order in Council</heading><made.at>At Wellington this 2nd day of March 2026</made.at><made.present>Present:<brk/>Her Excellency the Governor-General in Council</made.present></made></cover><front id="LMS1573992"><pursuant><para><text>This order is made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM6784026" id="LMS1574025">sections 452</extref> and <extref href="DLM6784028" id="LMS1574026">453</extref> of the <leg-title href="DLM6783102" id="LMS1577739">Social Security Act 2018</leg-title></citation> and <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM114207" id="LMS1574027">sections 15</extref> and <extref href="DLM114216" id="LMS1574028">16</extref> of the <leg-title href="DLM113923" id="LMS1577740">New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</leg-title></citation> on the advice and with the consent of the Executive Council.</text></para></pursuant></front><contents><heading>Contents</heading><toc/></contents><body id="LMS1574002" prov-type="clause"><heading>Order</heading><prov id="LMS1573993" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">1</label><heading>Title</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>This order is the Social Security (Rates of Benefits and Allowances) Order 2026.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1573994" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">2</label><heading>Commencement</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>This order comes into force on 1 April 2026, but <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574000" id="LMS1574029">clause 7</intref></citation> comes into force immediately after <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1573997" id="LMS1577741">clauses 4</intref>, <intref href="LMS1573998" id="LMS1577742">5</intref>, and <intref href="LMS1573999" id="LMS1577743">6</intref></citation>.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1573996" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">3</label><heading>Interpretation</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>In this order, <def-term id="LMS1573995">commencement date</def-term> means 1 April 2026.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1573997" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">4</label><heading>Application</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes">1</label><para><text>In accordance with <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM6784028" id="LMS1574031">section 453(5)</extref> of the Social Security Act 2018</citation>, <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1573998" id="LMS1574032">clause 5</intref></citation> applies to benefits (as defined in that Act) payable on and after the commencement date.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">2</label><para><text>In accordance with <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM114207" id="LMS1574033">section 15(6)</extref> of the New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</citation>, <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1573999" id="LMS1574034">clause 6</intref></citation> applies to New Zealand superannuation payable on and after the commencement date.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">3</label><para><text>In accordance with <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM6784026" id="LMS1574035">section 452(4)</extref> of the Social Security Act 2018</citation>, <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574000" id="LMS1574036">clause 7</intref></citation> applies to benefits, allowances, and entitlements payable on and after the commencement date.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1573998" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">5</label><heading>Mandatory adjustments under section 453 of Social Security Act 2018</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>In each provision of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM6783102" id="LMS1574037">Social Security Act 2018</leg-title></citation> listed in the first column of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574004" id="LMS1577744">Part 1</intref> of Schedule 1</citation> of this order, replace the amount set out opposite to that provision in the second column with the amount set out opposite to that provision in the third column.</text></para></subprov></prov.body><notes><amends-note><amends-effective><date>2026-04-01</date></amends-effective><amends-affect><citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM6783102" id="LMS1578427">Social Security Act 2018</leg-title></citation></amends-affect><amends-text>Clauses 5 and 7(1).</amends-text></amends-note></notes></prov><prov id="LMS1573999" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">6</label><heading>Mandatory adjustments under sections 15 and 16 of New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>In each provision of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM113923" id="LMS1574039">New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</leg-title></citation> listed in the first column of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574006" id="LMS1577745">Part 2</intref> of Schedule 1</citation> of this order, replace the amount set out opposite to that provision in the second column with the amount set out opposite to that provision in the third column.</text></para></subprov></prov.body><notes><amends-note><amends-effective><date>2026-04-01</date></amends-effective><amends-affect><citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM113923" id="LMS1578428">New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</leg-title></citation></amends-affect><amends-text>See clauses 6 and 7(2)-(3).</amends-text></amends-note></notes></prov><prov id="LMS1574000" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">7</label><heading>Discretionary increases under section 452 of Social Security Act 2018</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes">1</label><para><text>In each provision of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM6783102" id="LMS1574041">Social Security Act 2018</leg-title></citation> listed in the first column of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574009" id="LMS1577746">Part 1</intref> of Schedule 2</citation> of this order, replace the amount set out opposite to that provision in the second column with the amount set out opposite to that provision in the third column.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">2</label><para><text>In the provision of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM113923" id="LMS1574043">New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</leg-title></citation> listed in the first column of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574011" id="LMS1577747">Part 2</intref> of Schedule 2</citation> of this order, replace the amount set out opposite to that provision in the second column with the amount set out opposite to that provision in the third column.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">3</label><para><text>In the provision of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM113923" id="LMS1574045">New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001</leg-title></citation> listed in the first column of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1574013" id="LMS1577748">Part 3</intref> of Schedule 2</citation> of this order, replace the amount set out opposite to that provision in the second column with the amount set out opposite to that provision in the third column.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1574001" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">8</label><heading>Revocation</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>The <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="LMS1025754" id="LMS1574047">Social Security (Rates of Benefits and Allowances) Order 2025</leg-title></citation> (SL 2025/9) is revoked.</text></para></subprov></prov.body><notes><amends-note><amends-effective><date>2026-04-01</date></amends-effective><amends-affect><citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="LMS1025754" id="LMS1578092">Social Security (Rates of Benefits and Allowances) Order 2025</leg-title></citation></amends-affect></amends-note></notes></prov></body><schedule.group><schedule id="LMS1574007" prov-type="clause" schedule.heading.continue="no" series="statutory-regulation" toc="yes" type="schedule" date.as.at="2026-03-02" date.first.valid="2026-04-01" gazette-only="no" imperial="no" date.gazetted="2026-03-05" date.signed="2026-03-02" sr.no="36" year="2026" date.terminated="nulldate" sr.type="order"><label denominator="yes">1</label><empowering-prov><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1573998" id="LMS1574048">cls 5</intref>, <intref href="LMS1573999" id="LMS1574049">6</intref></citation></empowering-prov><heading>Mandatory adjustments</heading><schedule.misc><head1 id="LMS1574004" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">Part 1</label><heading>CPI adjustments to social security benefits and allowances</heading><para><legtable><summary>The following table is medium in size and has 3 columns. Column 1 is headed Provision amended and includes subheadings. Column 2 is headed Old amount ($). Column 3 is headed New amount ($).</summary><table align="left" colsep="0" fontsize="9.5" frame="none" id="LMS1574003" leading="10.5" rowsep="0"><tgroup cols="5"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.12*"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="12.05pt"/><colspec colname="col5" colwidth="1.44*"/><colspec colname="COLSPEC1" colwidth="12.05pt"/><colspec align="right" colname="COLSP